he%20government%20itself%20might%20also%20have%20been%20a%20target%20of%20those%20anticompetitive%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20summer%20of%202021%20%E2%80%94%20a%20little%20more%20than%20a%20year%20after%20news%20broke%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsolarwinds-hack-explained-government-agencies-cyber-security-2020-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESolarWinds%20hack%3C%2Fa%3E%20breached%20several%20government%20agencies%20%E2%80%94%20Microsoft%20pledged%20to%20give%20the%20government%20%24150%20billion%20over%20the%20coming%20five%20years%20to%20upgrade%20its%20digital%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20the%20federal%20government%20needs%20to%20obtain%20services%20through%20a%20competitive%20bidding%20process%2C%20but%20the%20deal%20terms%20were%20hard%20to%20pass%20up.%20Microsoft%20offered%20the%20government%20access%20to%20its%20G5%20security%20capabilities%20free%20for%20the%20first%20year%20as%20well%20as%20consultants%20to%20help%20install%20the%20products%2C%20ProPublica%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20catch%20was%20that%20once%20an%20agency%20committed%20to%20Microsoft's%20services%20they%20were%20essentially%20tied%20to%20them.%20Microsoft%20imposed%20steep%20fees%20on%20customers%20who%20wanted%20to%20shift%20to%20a%20competitor.%20The%20goal%20was%20to%20%26quot%3Bspin%20the%20meter%26quot%3B%20for%20Azure%20and%20help%20it%20gain%20market%20dominance%20over%20its%20competitor%2C%20Amazon%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ea%20sales%20representative%20for%20Microsoft%20told%20ProPublica.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20legal%20experts%20view%20the%20deal%20as%20venturing%20into%20murky%20antitrust%20territory%2C%20particularly%20regarding%20laws%20against%20gratuitous%20service%20agreements.%20These%20allow%20the%20federal%20government%20to%20receive%20services%20from%20other%20parties%20as%20long%20as%20no%20compensation%20is%20involved.%20However%2C%20legal%20expert%20James%20Nagle%2C%20who%20specializes%20in%20the%20federal%20contracting%20process%2C%20told%20ProPublica%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20truly%20gratuitous.%20There's%20another%20agenda%20in%20the%20works.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20say%20the%20blame%20should%20fall%20solely%20on%20the%20federal%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20Microsoft%20did%20does%20not%20count%20as%20an%20illegal%20monopoly%20because%20the%20government%20could%20have%20switched%20to%20a%20different%20vendor%2C%26quot%3B%20Peter%20Cohan%2C%20associate%20professor%20of%20practice%20in%20management%20at%20Babson%20College%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20by%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BArguably%2C%20the%20government%20should%20have%20put%20the%20cybersecurity%20contract%20out%20for%20bid%20to%20other%20rivals%20rather%20than%20signing%20up%20for%20G5%20after%20receiving%20the%20free%20consulting%20services%20from%20Microsoft.%20It%20is%20possible%20that%20other%20cybersecurity%20companies%20could%20have%20bid%20to%20cover%20some%20or%20all%20the%20government's%20cost%20to%20switch%20from%20Microsoft%20to%20another%20vendor%2C%20which%20might%20have%20charged%20the%20government%20less%20than%20G5%20rates.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteve%20Faehl%2C%20the%20company's%20security%20leader%20for%20federal%20business%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20ProPublica%20that%20the%20company's%20%26quot%3Bsole%20goal%20during%20this%20period%20was%20to%20support%20an%20urgent%20request%20by%20the%20Administration%20to%20enhance%20the%20security%20posture%20of%20federal%20agencies%20who%20were%20continuously%20being%20targeted%20by%20sophisticated%20nation-state%20threat%20actors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-anti-competitive-practices-ftc-khan-biden-big-tech-2024-11%5C%22%3EBus